  "doc_id": "27121",
  "text": "Three studies documented the availability and/or use of intellectual resources such as hypertension treatment guidelines. In South Africa, Daniel and colleagues [CITATION_1] , observed ambivalence towards the South African hypertension treatment guidelines noting \"that physicians do not regularly consult the guidelines citing insufficient resources and time, overcrowded clinics, decreasing staff, and few opportunities for continuing medical education (CME).\" Parker and colleagues [CITATION_2] also observed that in South Africa, physicians were not conversant with the contents of the guidelines. In cases of adverse drug reactions, Yusuf and Balogun [CITATION_3] observed that there was no 'institutional system in place to monitor, detect and document adverse drug reactions among patients on anti-hypertensive drug therapy.'",
